I remember the days of saving up for my $100 trim at Perry, the Aveda salon downtown.  I've had bangs, the curly "be curly", a pedicure, facial, yada yada waste of time and money! While I will never be over the delicious smell of Aveda products and continue splurging whenever I can afford it, no longer will I pay $25 for the extra blow dry!!! Nope, now I pay $25 for all of the bells and whistles at El y Ella.   In this no appointment, hip Mexico City style salon, you can walk in and walk out with a banging new do in about 45 minutes.  A complimentary dry is part of the package and while I might stop at "Perry" for some rosemary mint shampoo, that's about it.  I've found my spot!

