I can honestly say that you would've never caught me in this place if it hadn't been for my boyfriend suggesting it as one of our first dates.  The things that scared me away: valet parking and an overcrowded parking lot and the assumed pretentious wine snobs that frequent the area.  Of course, I was right about these concerns when I actually tried the place.  However....that doesn't mean that it can't be enjoyed with the right company.  The wine choices are unbeatable and they have a great app menu, of which I highly recommend the bruchetta (you can choose different several different toppings for one order and they were all equally delicious).  It's a great place to chat with friends, or go on a weeknight to grab some vino.  I'm not dying to go back anytime soon, so it's not a favorite for me.  However, I can see how some people would make this wine bar a regular stop.

